1 Section 1. Section 71-1572, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 71-1572 Sections 71-1572 to 71-15,170 and section 2 of this act
4 shall be known and may be cited as the Nebraska Housing Agency Act.
5 Sec. 2. (1) For purposes of this section:
6 (a) Bed bug means a member of the Cimicidae family of parasitic
7 insects; and
8 (b) Pest control professional means a person licensed as a
9 commercial applicator under the Pesticide Act.
10 (2) A housing agency for a city of the metropolitan class shall have
11 the following responsibilities relating to bed bugs:
12 (a) Prior to renting a dwelling unit, the housing agency shall
13 visually inspect the unit for any evidence of the presence of bed bugs,
14 which may be indicated by observation of a living bed bug, bed bug
15 carapace, eggs or egg casings, or brownish or blood spotting on linens,
16 mattresses, or furniture;
17 (b) The housing agency shall not show, rent, or lease to a
18 prospective tenant any vacant dwelling unit that the housing agency knows
19 or reasonably suspects has a current bed bug infestation;
20 (c) Prior to renting a dwelling unit, the housing agency shall
21 disclose to a prospective tenant if an adjacent unit or units are
22 currently infested with or are being treated for bed bugs;
23 (d) Upon notification by a person who finds or reasonably suspects a
24 bed bug infestation in a dwelling unit or common area of the premises,
25 the housing agency shall:
26 (i) Acknowledge the complaint within five days after notification of
27 the suspected infestation;
28 (ii) Inspect or obtain investigatory services from a pest control
29 professional within five days after notification;
30 (iii) Upon a determination of an infestation and within fourteen
31 days after notification, obtain and provide remedial services from a pest
