2 (iv) Inspect or obtain investigatory services of a pest control
3 professional in connection with any unit directly adjacent to, above, or
4 below the dwelling unit or common area from which the original report
5 came within five days after notification;
6 (v) Provide tenants with reasonable notice in advance of entering a
7 dwelling unit for purposes of inspection, bed bug remediation, or
8 monitoring in connection with a bed bug complaint;
9 (vi) Provide all tenants of units affected by a bed bug complaint
10 with notice of the pest control professional's determination in
11 connection with such unit within five days after receipt of information
12 from the pest control professional; and
13 (vii) Maintain a written record of all complaints and control
14 measures provided, including reports of chemicals applied and other
15 remedies provided by the pest control professional. Such records shall be
16 maintained for two years; and
17 (e) The housing agency shall be responsible for the costs of
18 investigating and remediating any bed bug infestation.
19 Sec. 3. Original section 71-1572, Revised Statutes Cumulative
20 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
